  "body": "use react-0.14.5\n\nin the examples/basic-click-counter/index.html\n\nchange the `handleClick` method: \n\n```\nhandleClick: function () {\n          this.setState({clickCount: this.state.clickCount+1});\n          this.setState({clickCount: this.state.clickCount+1});\n}\n```\n\nand add `componentDidMount` method:\n\n```\ncomponentDidMount: function(){\n  setTimeout(function(){\n    this.handleClick()\n  }.bind(this), 2000)\n}\n```\n\nIf I click  &lt;h2&gt; element, the `setState` invoked twice, and the `render` invoked one time. But If the `setState` invoked in `setTimeout` callback, the `render` invoked multi times.\n",
